oakcurric:unit-3264
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Hot desert and cold environments"@en ;
  curric:slug "hot-desert-and-cold-environments" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit teaches pupils about the location, characterisitics, opprtunities and
  challenges associated with one global environment, either hot deserts or cold
  environments. Pupils will also learn about plant and animal adaptation and about issues
  facing their chosen environment."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils can build on their knowledge of small-scale ecosystems and
  large-scale biomes to develop a comprehensive understanding of a chosen extreme environment,
  either a hot desert or a cold environment. Understanding the connections between physical and
  human processes will provide a foundation in studying subsequent units.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3264-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3264-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3264-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3264-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3264-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3264-6 ;
  curric:id "3264"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.291161Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-geography-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-risk-and-resilience ,
    oakcurric:thread-physical-systems-and-processes .

oakcurric:unit-3301
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Jakarta: case study of a major city in a Newly Emerging Economy"@en ;
  curric:slug "jakarta-case-study-of-a-major-city-in-a-newly-emerging-economy" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit teaches pupils about the development, importance and characteristics of
  Jakarta, an emerging country/NEE. Pupils will study the opportunities and challenges
  associated with the growth of the city, considering issues such as housing, services, the
  environment and sustainability."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils can build on their knowledge of global urbanisation from the
  previous unit to develop a deeper understanding of the processes and patterns in an emerging
  city/NEE. In the subsequent unit, pupils can contrast Jakarta with the city of Liverpool.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3301-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3301-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3301-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3301-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3301-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3301-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3301-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3301-8 ;
  curric:id "3301"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.384355Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-geography-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-inequality ,
    oakcurric:thread-globalisation-and-interconnection ,
    oakcurric:thread-human-systems-and-processes ,
    oakcurric:thread-representation-and-identity .

oakcurric:unit-3286
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Climate change"@en ;
  curric:slug "climate-change" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit teaches pupils about the evidence, causes and impacts of climate change.
  Pupils learn that climate change is not just a recent trend but that it has occurred
  natuarlly over geological time. Pupils will also learn about the strategic options
  associated with mitigation and adaptation."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit naturally builds on pupils prior knowledge gained from studying
  weather hazards in the previous unit. Climate change underpins many of the issues considered
  in subsequent units, such as global economic development, energy resources and urban
  planning.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3286-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3286-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3286-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3286-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3286-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3286-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3286-7 ;
  curric:id "3286"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.528471Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-geography-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-risk-and-resilience ,
    oakcurric:thread-sustainability-and-climate-change ,
    oakcurric:thread-physical-systems-and-processes .

oakcurric:unit-3701
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Global inequalities"@en ;
  curric:slug "global-inequalities" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit teaches pupils about global economic development. Pupils learn how,
  using a variety of measures, economic development is unequal and how this is reflected in
  demographic characteristics. Pupils learn about the causes and consequences of inequality
  and consider how they can be reduced."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit enables pupils to build on their global locational knowledge to
  consider patterns of economic development and inequality. Previously taught units on hazards
  help to inform an understanding of the causes of global inequality. Subsequent units build on
  this overview by considering resources, such as food, water and energy.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3701-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3701-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3701-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3701-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3701-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3701-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3701-7 ;
  curric:id "3701"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.530996Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-geography-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-globalisation-and-interconnection ,
    oakcurric:thread-human-systems-and-processes ,
    oakcurric:thread-representation-and-identity .

oakcurric:unit-3292
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Places and people in the UK"@en ;
  curric:slug "places-and-people-in-the-uk" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit teaches pupils about the human geography of the UK. Pupils learn about
  population distribution, the location of cities and the impacts of migration. Pupils also
  learn about the role of the UK government and the EU and the importance of globalisation
  in the UK's changing economy."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils can build on their previous locational knowledge of the UK from KS3
  and begin to apply it to key economic themes, influenced by policies at home and abroad. This
  unit forms a solid foundation for further in-depth study of human geography in subsequent
  units.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3292-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3292-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3292-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3292-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3292-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3292-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3292-7 ;
  curric:id "3292"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.533593Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-geography-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-inequality ,
    oakcurric:thread-globalisation-and-interconnection .

oakcurric:unit-3288
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Coastal landscapes"@en ;
  curric:slug "coastal-landscapes" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit teaches pupils about coastal processes and landforms. Pupils will learn
  about the physical processes operating at the coast and about the formation of distinctive
  landforms of coastal erosion and deposition. Pupils will also learn about the importance
  and options of coastal management."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils can build on their previous knowledge of the UK's physical
  geography and geology by focusing on processes and landforms at the coast. Pupils can also
  make comparisons with river landscapes, studied in the previous unit. Knowledge from this
  unit will support the fieldwork unit.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3288-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3288-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3288-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3288-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3288-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3288-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3288-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3288-8 ;
  curric:id "3288"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.621993Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-geography-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-risk-and-resilience ,
    oakcurric:thread-sustainability-and-climate-change ,
    oakcurric:thread-physical-systems-and-processes .

oakcurric:unit-3698
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Liverpool: changes in a UK city"@en ;
  curric:slug "liverpool-changes-in-a-uk-city" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit teaches pupils about the geography of Liverpool, one of the UK's most
  important cities. Pupils learn about Liverpool's location and importance at different
  scales and about its characteristics. Pupils will learn about the factors leading to
  economic, social and environmental change."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils can build on their locational knowledge of cities in the UK and on
  the study of cities at KS3 to better their understanding of the factors and processes
  contributing to the characteristics and development of Liverpool. In subsequent units, pupils
  will be able to compare and contrast Liverpool with Jakarta, a city in an emerging
  country/NEE.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3698-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3698-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3698-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3698-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3698-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3698-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3698-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3698-8 ;
  curric:id "3698"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.700748Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-geography-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-inequality ,
    oakcurric:thread-globalisation-and-interconnection ,
    oakcurric:thread-representation-and-identity .

oakcurric:unit-3072
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Tropical rainforest"@en ;
  curric:slug "tropical-rainforest" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit teaches pupils about the tropical rainforest biome. Pupils learn about
  the biotic and abiotic characteristics of tropical rainforests and the adaptations of
  plants and animals. Pupils will also learn about the importance of tropical rainforests
  and how they are under threat."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils can build on their knowledge of ecosystems and biomes to develop
  their understanding of the tropical rainforest biome, its distribution, characteristics and
  threats. This unit builds on the knowledge gained earlier and enables comparisons to be made
  when studying future units on hot desert and cold environments.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3072-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3072-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3072-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3072-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3072-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3072-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3072-7 ;
  curric:id "3072"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.855471Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-geography-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-risk-and-resilience ,
    oakcurric:thread-sustainability-and-climate-change ,
    oakcurric:thread-physical-systems-and-processes .

oakcurric:unit-3073
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Tropical rainforest and taiga biomes"@en ;
  curric:slug "tropical-rainforest-and-taiga-biomes" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit teaches pupils about tropical rainforest and taiga biomes. Pupils learn
  about its biotic and abiotic characteristics, the adaptations of plants and animals and
  the threats facing its biodiversity. The unit considers opposing views on protecting and
  exploiting resources."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils can build on their knowledge of ecosystems and biomes developed in
  earlier lessons to develop an understanding of the characteristics and threats facing
  tropical rainforest and taiga biomes. Pupils will be able to apply their knowledge in
  subsequent units focusing on global development and resource management.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3073-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3073-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3073-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3073-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3073-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3073-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3073-7 ;
  curric:id "3073"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.863163Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-geography-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-physical-systems-and-processes .

oakcurric:unit-3640
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Coastal, river and glacial landscapes"@en ;
  curric:slug "coastal-river-and-glacial-landscapes" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit, comprising of three variants, teaches pupils about processes and
  landforms associated with coastal, river and glacial landscapes. Pupils will learn about
  the formative processes involved in creating distinctive landforms and of the need for
  management."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils can build on their previous knowledge of the UK's physical
  geography and geology by focusing on physical processes and landforms in landscape
  development. Pupils may draw upon their knowledge gained in the subsequent unit on fieldwork.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3640-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3640-2 ,
