oakcurric:unit-3694
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Geographical and statistics skills"@en ;
  curric:slug "geographical-and-statistics-skills" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit teaches pupils about geographical skills. Pupils will learn how to
  identify, describe and analyse atlas and OS maps at different scales. They will also learn
  how to construct and interpret photos, diagrams, graphs and thematic maps. Pupils will
  also learn numerical and statistical skills."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils need to apply geographical skills throughout the course and this
  unit can be dipped into at any stage and as many times as necessary. This unit works well in
  association with the previous fieldwork unit as this is the most concentrated area of skills
  application in the GCSE course. In subsequent units, pupils can continue to practice their
  geographical skills.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3694-1 ,
