oakcurric:unit-3697
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Global biomes"@en ;
  curric:slug "global-biomes" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit teaches pupils about ecosystems and biomes at different scales. Pupils
  learn about the factors influencing biome distribution and the physical systems and
  processes regulating them. Pupils will also learn about the impact of population growth
  and resource extraction on biomes."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils can build on their knowledge of biomes and ecosystems developed in
  KS3 to develop a better understanding of the processes and factors influencing their
  distribution. Teaching the unit as this stage allows pupils to use the knowledge gained in
  subsequent units on the tropical rainforest and taiga biomes. It also allows pupils to use
  their knowledge as a context for filedwork studies later in the course.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3697-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3697-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3697-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3697-4 ;
  curric:id "3697"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.189724Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-geography-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-physical-systems-and-processes .

oakcurric:unit-3285
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Weather hazards"@en ;
  curric:slug "weather-hazards" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit teaches pupils about weather hazards at the global and national (UK)
  scales. Pupils learn about global atmospheric circulation before focusing on the
  formation, impacts and responses to tropical storms. Pupils also learn about extreme
  weather events in the UK."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils can build on their knowledge of weather and climate developed in
  KS3 to consider the global context before focusing on tropical cyclones. Teaching the unit at
  this stage enables pupils to apply knowledge of hazards learned earlier in the year to the
  weather. It also allows pupils to use their knowledge of weather hazards when addressing
  development issues in subsequent units.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3285-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3285-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3285-3 ,
