oakcurric:unit-3306
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Energy"@en ;
  curric:slug "energy" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit teaches pupils about different energy resources, their extraction and
  uses. Pupils learn about the different types of energy, the factors affecting extraction
  and the patterns and inequalites associated with production and consumption. Pupils also
  learn about energy futures."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils can build on their previous knowledge of global economic geography
  and the study of urbanisation to develop a better understanding of patterns and inequalities
  in global energy production and consumption. The placement of this unit towards the end of
  Year 11 reflects the high-level concepts that underpin this unit""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3306-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3306-2 ,
