oakcurric:unit-3284
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Natural and tectonic hazards"@en ;
  curric:slug "natural-and-tectonic-hazards" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit teaches pupils about natural and tectonic hazards, their location,
  causes and effects. Pupils learn about the different types of hazard before focusing on
  earthquakes and volcanoes. Pupils will learn about tectonic processes, hazard impacts and
  the options for mitigation and adaptation."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils can build on their knowledge of earthquakes and volcanoes studied
  at KS3, and on their global locational knowledge to develop a more in-depth understanding of
  natural hazards. Having studied physical systems and processes at the global scale, pupils
  can go on to learn about smaller-scale landscape processes, such as rivers and coasts.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3284-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3284-2 ,
