oakcurric:unit-3300
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Patterns of global urbanisation"@en ;
  curric:slug "patterns-of-global-urbanisation" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit teaches pupils about patterns and trends in global urbanisation. Pupils
  study regional variations, patterns and growth in urbanisation and the development of
  megacities. Pupils also learn about the changing factors affecting growth, urban land uses
  and sustainable urban living."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils can build on their knowledge of global urban geography from KS3 to
  develop a greater depth of understanding of the processes and consequences of urbanisation.
  This unit sets the scene and provides an appropriate context for the more detailed city case
  study (Jakarta) in the next unit.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3300-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3300-2 ,
