oakcurric:unit-3289
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "River landscapes"@en ;
  curric:slug "river-landscapes" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit teaches pupils about river processes and landforms. Pupils will learn
  about the physical processes operating in rivers and about the formation of distinctive
  landforms of river erosion and deposition. Pupils will also learn about the importance and
  options of river management."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils can build on their previous knowledge of the UK's physical
  geography by studying river processes and landforms. Teaching this unit provides pupils with
  a template to studying physical environments by considering processes, landforms and
  management. This enables comparison to be made with coasts in the next unit. Knowledge gained
  will also support the fieldwork unit.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3289-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3289-2 ,
