oakcurric:unit-3295
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Global variations in economic development"@en ;
  curric:slug "global-variations-in-economic-development" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit teaches pupils about global economic development. Pupils learn how,
  using a variety of measures, economic development is unequal and how this is reflected in
  demographic characteristics. Pupils learn about the causes and consequences of inequality
  and consider how they can be reduced."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit enables pupils to build on their global locational knowledge to
  consider patterns of economic development and inequality. Previously taught units on hazards
  help to inform an understanding of the causes of global inequality. Subsequent units build on
  this overview by considering resources, such as food, water and energy.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3295-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3295-2 ,
