oakcurric:unit-3303
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Global pattern of resources"@en ;
  curric:slug "global-pattern-of-resources" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit, comprising of three variants, teaches pupils about global inequalities
  in food, water and energy production and consumption. Pupils learn about resource security
  and about sustainable futures."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on the earlier unit which focuses on resources in the UK
  and enables pupils to develop a broader understanding of global inequalities in resource
  production and consumption. Having considered the global overview, pupils opt to study two
  resources in greater depth. This unit can support pupils in the subsequent unit on issue
  evaluation.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3303-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3303-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3303-3 ,
